   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Due to how properties are tracked, some unsatisfiable scripts may pass the `IsSane()` checks. This is an issue as we would treat some unspendable scripts as safe. Fix this by explicitly checking a satisfaction exists when checking for sanity.\r\n\r\nThis bug was exposed due to a check added in #22838 (https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/22838#discussion_r1226859880) that triggered a fuzz crash (https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/22838#issuecomment-1612510057).",
